  "name": "Horrid Wilting",
  "ownership": {
    "default": 0
  },
  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You draw the moisture from every creature of your choice in a 30-foot cube centered on a point you choose within range. Each creature in that area must make a <strong>Constitution saving throw</strong>. Constructs and undead aren't affected, and plants and water elementals make this saving throw with disadvantage. A creature takes <strong>16d8 necrotic damage</strong> on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p><p>Nonmagical plants in the area that aren't creatures, such as trees and shrubs, wither and die instantly.</p>",
